      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEORGE ALEXIS (1) finished eighth last time at this track but could not have been more impressive a few runs back in his slick 23.77 win at this track over 407m. Looks the one to beat on best figures. FARMOR SENIOR (3) has a strong winning strike-rate this journey here having won two of four starts. Missed the frame latest (24.41) when fourth over 407m at this track in a Grade 5. Can hit the frame with the right run. JACKPOT JUNIOR (8) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 407m behind Gus The Great (24.29) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Bold showing expected. SHE'S FULL ON (2) did a good job to finish second last time out over 407m at this track (23.91) in a Grade 5, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
